        <translation>
            <line n="a1">
                <tr>In the first regnal year, on the thirtieth [day] of the <hi>Rāp</hi> Month [= the
                    last month of the year], in the night [of the feast] <hi>Rāp</hi>, for the Appeasers
                    (?)</tr>
            </line>
            <line n="a2">
                <tr>alcohol for drinking went [out] [in the amount of] eight <hi>tau</hi>. | The lord
                    ordered [to give] two <hi>tau</hi> of alcohol to the women, | [and an amount of] one
                    <hi>cāk</hi>, nine <hi>tau</hi> to the planters, |</tr>
            </line>
            <line n="a3">
                <tr>two <hi>tau</hi> towards <hi>Tarmamitrorśa</hi> (or: <hi>Tarmamitre</hi>, the
                    <hi>Orśa</hi>) | (For ...)</tr>
            </line>
            <line n="a4">
                <tr>again alcohol for drinking went [out] [in the amount of] one <hi>cāk</hi>, one
                    <hi>tau</hi>.</tr>
            </line>
        </translation>
        <comments>
            <comment id="n1" type="lingcomment">Note the depalatalization in <hi>menne</hi>.</comment>
            <comment id="n2" type="philcomment">The translation follows <ref
                litRef="ogiharaandpinault2010" pageRange="180"/>.</comment>
            <comment id="n3" type="remarks">Provisorial pressmark;</comment>
            <comment id="n4" type="remarks">Photograph published in <ref
                litRef="nationallibraryofchina2006" pageRange="97"/> without press mark; precise find
                spot is unknown, "Tumšuq" as indicated by the publishers is possible.</comment>
            <comment id="n5" type="lingcomment">
                <hi>kṣutsa</hi> for <hi>kṣuntsa</hi> or <hi>kṣuṃntsa</hi> probably reflects the loss of
                the nasal rather than a simple misspelling (<ref litRef="ogiharaandpinault2010"
                    pageRange="176f"/>.).</comment>
            <comment id="n6" type="philcomment">For the feast <hi>Rāp</hi> 'New Year's Eve' (?), see
                <ref litRef="pinault2008" pageRange="363f"/>., <ref litRef="ogiharaandpinault2010"
                    pageRange="188-192"/> and <ref litRef="adams2013a" pageRange="573f"/>.</comment>
            <comment id="n7" type="philcomment">For the meaning of <hi>sänmassu</hi>* adj. 'calm' &gt;
                'people pertaining to the appeasing ritual', see the discussion by <ref
                    litRef="ogiharaandpinault2010" pageRange="184f"/>.</comment>
            <comment id="n8" type="lingcomment">
                <hi>sarātsaṃts</hi> is a gen.pl. of a nomen agentis in -<hi>ntsa sarāntsa</hi>* made
                from <lemmaRef lemma="E_B_sār_G"/> 'to plant' (<ref litRef="ogiharaandpinault2010"
                    pageRange="185"/>).</comment>
